Scam ,,,scam,,,,scammm
Wazbee is a place where you're guaranteed to have your wallet wiped out. If you pay out to these scammers, you'll get no 24-hour cashback, and no bonus. It's pretty impossible to achieve. For the past three weeks, the session has been a series of deposit losses, deposit losses, and losses. Absolutely nothing, tons of empty spins. But what's really bothering me is that the 24-hour cashback isn't added as the name suggests, and the false information on the website is also present. Every day, after 24 hours, cashback is automatically added after calculating losses, etc. They haven't refunded me anything in the form of cashback for three weeks. They're justifying this by saying that cashback is calculated not every 24 hours, but from the day I open the account. This isn't mentioned in the description. Secondly, in these three weeks, these scammers haven't even added a €1 bonus. Their response is that the bonus is ineligible. I haven't lost enough. People should ignore this German mess.

Aug 21, 2025
a Major Plus
Game Selection is a Major Plus: You're not going to get bored here. Wazbee seems to have a massive library of games, which is great if you're someone who likes to switch between slots, classic table games, and live dealer action. This variety is often a key factor for a good long-term experience.
* Fast Withdrawals: This is a huge deal for any online gambler. The speed at which you can get your winnings is a true measure of a casino's quality. Wazbee's reputation for fast withdrawals is a very positive sign.
* 24/7 Customer Support: If you have an issue, you want it fixed immediately. The availability of 24/7 live chat is a sign that the casino is serious about player satisfaction. It's reassuring to know help is always available.
* Crypto and Fiat Options: The ability to use both traditional money and cryptocurrencies gives you flexibility. If you're a crypto user, this is a big convenience.
The Things to Be Cautious About:
* Curacao License: While a license from Curacao is better than nothing, it's not the most stringent regulator. This means that if you run into a serious dispute with the casino, you might have fewer avenues for recourse compared to a casino licensed by the MGA or UKGC. It's an important detail for peace of mind.
* Wagering Requirements on Bonuses: The bonuses may look great, but the fine print is what matters. Be prepared to read the terms and conditions very carefully. Some reviews suggest that the wagering requirements for certain games (like table games) are very high, which can make it difficult to actually cash out any winnings from the bonus money.

No compensatory payouts after January 2025, despite large deposits.
Paper-only bonuses – for months, I received the standard response: "This isn't for you, contact me after your next session." Only after three hours of arguing in chat did I receive 100 free spins (around €10) and a €30 bonus – practically useless.
Chats and data – a disaster – the casino refuses to share my chat history. Transactions don't display correctly. I can only verify my deposits using my own email confirmations.

This means outcomes are entirely based on chance, and unfortunately, luck doesn’t always go in a player’s favor.

We’d also like to stress that we don’t have any influence over when bonuses, jackpots, or bigger wins occur. Every spin is independent and fair, even if the results can sometimes feel discouraging during an unlucky streak.

We always encourage responsible play and recommend setting personal limits to keep the experience enjoyable.

Best regards,
Wazbee Team

No reasonable regulator allows this behaviour.

"Unfortunately our functionality does not allow us to set deposit limits".

No, you don't take responsible gambling seriously. You take avoiding responsible gambling seriously as that makes you more money. Wazbee chooses not to be cause it doesn't want people to gamble responsibly, it wants people to lose as much as possible. Why else would you avoid having the standard functionality?

In addition when someone says "permanent self exclusion" any responsible casino would not let them play. But not only dies Wazbee let them play, but it let's them play with no deposit limit.

That doesn't sound like someone that takes responsible gambling seriously to anyone - not even you.

Avoid - don't send withdrawals as claimed
Really disappointing experience with Wazbee. Opened an account and deposited, turned over quite a bit of money, tried to request a withdrawal (made around $200), withdrawal was approved and even showed up on their live stream of withdrawals, claiming it was sent in 4 minutes.

However, there was never any withdrawal sent - My crypto wallet isn't showing any pending transactions when I search on the blockchain explorer.

I asked live chat to provide me the transaction ID of the withdrawal, which they couldn't do - they couldn't even confirm if the withdrawal had been sent or not, promising someone would get back to me by email (which no one did of course).

Really disappointing to see the website blatantly lying to customers regarding their withdrawal processing times and whether they have actually processed withdrawals when they claim.

Further they have a very strict and vague turnover requirement before you can withdraw - far higher than any other casino I've seen. It's more than the 3x claimed here on the casino guru website - it actually varies from 6x to 15x depending what game you play.

Of course the website claims this is an 'anti-fraud' protection but we all know it's so no one can make a withdrawal.

Stay away. Dodgy website. Don't deposit, you won't be able to withdraw and worse, you will be lied to and have information withheld.

Jun 16, 2024
STAY AWAY! x3 WAGER ON EACH DEPOSIT & I'VE SPENT OVER AN HOUR TRYING TO VERIFY MY ACCOUNT!
THEY HAVE A x3 WAGER ON EACH OF YOUR DEPOSIT! You simply cannot deposit let's say 50 euros and withdraw it afterwards until you've made bets for 150 euros. UNBELIEVEBLE! They have a term that states "5.12 In cases where a player requests a withdraw without meeting the minimum turnover requirements, WazBee reserves the right to charge a 15% fee on the requested withdraw amount". Even though I told the support that I would like to request a withdraw with that 15% fee the support told me "You have to meet the wagering requirements of x3". SWAY AWAY FROM THIS WEBISTE! THEY SCAM FOLKS!

From my experience the RTP isn't the greatest and it eats your money pretty fast.

Their verification rules are stupid. Nowhere in their terms is written that they do not accept Revolut bank statements. Also when I had to verify my credit card the back side was declined just because I have to cover the CVV/CVC code with a piece of paper and not with a program such as paint etc. They don't ask for a selfie but rather you have to use your camera and scan your face ( haven't done that before, I don't see it as a problem but more as extra steps that are useless, because they can ask you for a photo of you. )

Not a big variety of game providers. ( And from the providers that they already have a lot of games are missing. )

They have a live chat support that wasn't very helpful. On some questions that I've asked their response was "You can try to do it and see if it works". And we call that 'support'.

The website design looks good but the images that they're using for the games are not the right size. Some of them look weird, stretch like someone was in a hurry to download/upload everything that had to be uploaded and it didn't matter if it looked good or not.

The EGTDigital provider doesn't work. The support told me to clean the cookies, try with a different browser or restart my PC and non of them worked. I didn't bother to ask them again because they weren't going to help me out.

My personal opinion is to stay away from this casino and find something that was founded before 2024 and has a good reputation among gamblers.

P.S: The fact that they make you wager your own money x3 without a applied bonus is NOT right! They should shut them down! STAY AWAY or Gamble on your own risk.

We take your concerns seriously and are committed to making the necessary changes. If you could provide your account details, we will thoroughly investigate your claims and make any necessary adjustments. Please contact our support team directly for further assistance.

Thank you for helping us improve.
